over to install and test software and network configurations. Although engagement environments are virtual, the user experience is identical to the resources provided by traditional hardware based server and desktop computers. Programs have used our virtual project space to perform alternatives analysis, user acceptance testing, baseline configuration development and estimating what Hardware/software resources are required for procurement.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/doctor.png\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1336\" alt=\"doctor\" src=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/doctor.png\" width=\"364\" height=\"280\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Evaluation</strong> – structured evaluations of technology, practices or tools to assess their potential impact for public health. Lab personnel review existing or planned informatics or IT tools to help programs integrate (if appropriate) new approaches.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Physical Collaboration Space</strong> – the Lab has a physical location with demonstration capabilities, large video display, SmartBoard technology, Windows and Mac OSX workstations in an enclaved local area network that allows programs to meet in person for brainstorming, social media campaigns, communication activities, training, focus groups, and software demonstrations.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Open Source Development Tools</strong> – The Lab hosts a set of software development collaboration tools at code.phiresearchlab.org. CODE has a source code repository (currently Subversion with additional repository types soon to come), issue tracking &amp; project management (JIRA) and blog/wiki/content management (Confluence) available for use by public health projects that need to collaborate with diverse partners. Projects can administer their own project spaces within these tools to best meet the needs of their development projects (e.g., add/change user permissions, design blog/wiki layout and content, share source and runtime files).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Consultation</strong> – The Lab’s cross-functional team is available for conversations to discuss and plan approaches to and strategies for particular informatics and technology questions. Programs have used the Lab to review environmental scanning and market research, investigate different architectural approaches and plan use of lab resources for prototyping and/or virtual project space.</p>','Services','','inherit','open','open','','1198-revision-18','','','2014-02-05 17:18:19','2014-02-05 17:18:19','',1198,'http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/?p=1430',0,'revision','',0),(1447,1,'2014-02-05 21:04:01','2014-02-05 21:04:01','Cras malesuada sem vitae nulla accumsan, nec placerat metus consectetur. Quisque lobortis ligula enim, in tempus odio mollis id. Praesent in erat quis odio scelerisque ultrices vitae ut eros. Sed in sodales enim. Nulla pellentesque eros sit amet facilisis accumsan. Nunc vel orci non dui consectetur aliquam et quis mi. Fusce tellus arcu, dictum vel orci non, cursus molestie eros. Praesent elit libero, suscipit eu auctor at, luctus non justo. Morbi id fringilla libero. In vulputate nibh turpis, vel facilisis lacus adipiscing non. Proin ullamcorper leo vitae dui elementum tempus. Fusce orci leo, scelerisque non pellentesque sed, iaculis ac augue. Nullam a dui at elit ornare elementum.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/kitty_12.png\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1407\" alt=\"kitty_12\" src=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/kitty_12.png\" width=\"364\" height=\"280\" /></a>Ut blandit nibh mauris, non tincidunt nulla porta et. Praesent nec turpis ullamcorper, commodo felis ut, ornare neque. Pellentesque luctus, nunc ut luctus euismod, elit tellus laoreet dolor, sed pulvinar nisi lectus non eros. Duis sagittis scelerisque lacinia. Ut eget risus quis nunc cursus dictum non in lorem. Fusce a sceleris