p://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/keyboard_steth.png\" width=\"263\" height=\"180\" /></a>The <strong>Informatics Innovation Unit (IIU)</strong> came into existence in 2007 as a physical collaboration Research and Development (R&amp;D) lab space created for the National Center for Public Health Informatics (NCPHI). Through the years, the IIU has grown exponentially not only in its capabilities, but also in its ability to serve the CDC community. Today, the IIU serves in excess of 20 programs each year in the quest to reduce costs, save time, and gain knowledge.\r\n\r\nPresently, the IIU is located within CDC\'s Center for Surveillance, Epidemiology, and Laboratory Services (CSELS) and is a resource to CDC and the public health community as it studies, prototypes, and tests new and innovative technology-based tools and resources in order to maximize programmatic public health impact. The IIU team examines new technologies, such as mobile devices, prototype software, and even robotics, to test their potential value to CDC and its public health partners. In addition to carrying out applied research, sharing evaluations, and developing prototypes, the IIU team provides consultation to CDC and its public health partners.\r\n\r\nNot surprisingly, the IIU team is comprised of individuals with significantly varied backgrounds and areas of expertise. These areas include hardware design, mobile software development, graphics/user experience, web-based application development, enterprise architecture, and clinical/public health informatics.','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','1760-revision-42','','','2014-02-21 21:35:22','2014-02-21 21:35:22','',1760,'http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/?p=1852',0,'revision','',0),(1854,1,'2014-02-24 16:41:06','2014-02-24 16:41:06','<style><!--\r\np {padding-bottom:.5em;} #line {height:1px; width:100%; background-color:#dddddd; margin-bottom:1em;}\r\n--></style>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-top: .7em; padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a href=\"?cat=139\">Structured Evaluations</a>   |   <a href=\"?cat=140\">Brief Reviews</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/tech_research.png\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1848\" alt=\"tech_research\" src=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/tech_research.png\" width=\"266\" height=\"178\" /></a>Overview blurb lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum.\r\n\r\nSed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem accusantium doloremque laudantium, totam rem aperiam, eaque ipsa quae ab illo inventore veritatis et quasi architecto beatae vitae dicta sunt explicabo. Nemo enim ipsam voluptatem quia voluptas sit aspernatur aut odit aut fugit, sed quia consequuntur magni dolores eos qui ratione voluptatem sequi nesciunt.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"?cat=139\">Structured Evaluations</a>:</strong> Formal testing and evaluation of technologies that have a potential impact on public health practice. These evaluations use a framework and template developed by the IIU team to develop a quantitative and qualitative review of how a technology can be useful for public health.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"?cat=140\">Brief Reviews</a>:</strong> Short, informal posts reviewing a specific technology, software application, or product. These reviews are more timely and do not follow the structured evaluation framework. The reviews cover pertinent information such as features, functionality, and recommendations.','Technology Reviews','','inherit','open','open','','1757-revision-16','','','2014-02-24 16:41:06','2014-02-24 16:41:06','',1757,'http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/?p=1854',0,'revision','',0),(1855,1,'2014-02-18 20:22:40','2014-02-18 20:22:40','Portfolio content.','Portfolio','','inherit','open','open','','1751-revision-2','','','2014-02-18 20:22:40','2014-02-18 20:22:40','',1751,'http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/?p=1855',0,'revision','',0),(1856,1,'2014-02-25 15:06:40','2014-02-25 15:06:40','<style><!--\np {padding-bottom:.5em;} #line {height:1px; width:100%; background-color:#dddddd; margin-bottom:1em;}\na.listing {color:  #017fae; }\n--></style>\n<p style=\"text-align: left; font-size: .8em; padding-top: .7em; padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a href=\"?page_id=1427\">MOBILE (APP LAB)</a> &nbsp;  |  &nbsp; <a href=\"?page_id=1763\" >WEB</a> &nbsp;  |  &nbsp; <a href=\"?page_id=1766\">WIREFRAMES &amp; MOCKUPS</a> &nbsp;  |  &nbsp; <a href=\"?page_id=1769\">EBOOKS</a></p>\n<a href=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/diagram.png\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1858\" alt=\"diagram\" src=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/diagram.png\" width=\"297\" height=\"199\" /></a>The Lab gains insight by designing and developing software to test new concepts and improve system requirements. These projects demonstrate a concept, test an approach, or experiment with a new technology.\n\nTypically, the Lab will work with one or more public health programs to develop prototype software that solves a specific public health problem.\n\nOur portfolio is grouped into the following categories:\n\n<strong><a href=\"?page_id=1427\" class=\"listing\">Mobile (App Lab):</a></strong> Mobile prototypes and apps created in collaboration with various public health programs. The Lab, CDC, &amp; its public health partners test and collaborate on innovative mobile apps for iOS-based devices (iPhone, iPad, etc.) and Android-based devices. We also plan to start creating prototypes for Windows 8 devices.<em> To access the mobile portion of our portfolio, a passcode is required. To request a passcode, please e-mail: <a href=\"mailto:informaticslab@cdc.gov\">informaticslab@cdc.gov</a></em>\n\n<strong><a href=\"?page_id=1763\">Web</a>:</strong> Web application prototypes. These prototypes are created in collaboration with various public health programs, and leverage numerous web technologies including HTML 5, Web API, jQuery, social media data, and more.\n\n<strong><a href=\"?page_id=1766\">Wireframes &amp; Mockups</a>:</strong> Wireframes are low-fidelity blueprints of the user interface (UI), and they help with planning the information architecture, layout, interaction design, and user experience of the application. Once the wireframe design has been finalized, we move to the mockup stage. Our mockups are typically high-fidelity, and closely illustrate the actual graphical look and feel of the UI. Some of our prototype engagements end at the initial wireframing and mockup stages. Wireframes and mockups can help a program explore a concept without necessarily developing an application.\n\n<strong><a href=\"?page_id=1769\">Ebooks</a>:</strong> We can assist public health programs who are interested in converting existing content into an electronic publication that\'s compatible with iBooks and all other ebook readers.','Portfolio','','inherit','open','open','','1751-autosave','','','2014-02-25 15:06:40','2014-02-25 15:06:40','',1751,'http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/?p=1856',0,'revision','',0),(1857,1,'2014-02-24 17:31:03','2014-02-24 17:31:03','<style><!--\r\np {padding-bottom:.5em;} #line {height:1px; width:100%; background-color:#dddddd; margin-bottom:1em;}\r\n--></style>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-top: .7em; padding-bottom: 1em;\"><a href=\"?cat=139\">Structured Evaluations</a>   |   <a href=\"?cat=140\">Brief Reviews</a></p>\r\n<a href=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/tech_research.png\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-1848\" alt=\"tech_research\" src=\"http://172.16.100.211/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/tech_resea